220170 		Fri, 7/31/2020, 1:00 PM - 6:00 PM
Council of Sections Business Meeting — Other Cmte/Business
Council of Sections
Chair(s): Ofer Harel, University of Connecticut
The Council of Sections Business Meeting will be held virtually on the afternoon of Friday, July 31, and divided into three separate one-hour sessions based on the COS Vice Chair assignments:

1:00 p.m. Eastern time
Vice Chair: Elizabeth Slate
Sections: Government Statistics, Social Statistics, Survey Research Methods, Statistical Computing, Statistical Graphics, Defense and National Security, Statistics in Sports, Statistical Learning and Data Science, Lifetime Data Analysis, Transportation Statistics (IG), Astrostatistics (IG), Quantum Computing in Statistics and Machine Learning (IG), and Text Analysis (IG)

3:00 p.m. Eastern time
Vice Chair: Phil Scinto
Sections: Biometrics, Biopharmaceutical, Statistics in Epidemiology, Teaching Statistics in the Health Sciences, Health Policy Statistics, Statistics and the Environment, Nonparametric Statistics, Statistical Programmers and Analysts, Statistics in Imaging, Mental Health Statistics, Medical Devices and Diagnostics, Genomics and Genetics, and Pharmacometrics (IG)

5:00 p.m. Eastern time
Vice Chair: Alyson Wilson
Sections: Quality & Productivity, Physical & Engineering Sciences, Risk Analysis, Statistical Education, Statistical Consulting, Bayesian Statistical Science, Business & Economic Statistics, Statistics in Marketing, Business Analytics/Statistics Education (IG), Uncertainty Quantification in Complex Systems (IG), Statistical Auditing (IG), and History of Statistics (IG)

If you have a conflict with the session assigned to your section you may attend one of the other sessions as content will be the same. If you cannot attend any of the sessions another officer from your section may attend in your place. Please notify ASA Staff Liaison, Rick Peterson if there is a change in the session you will attend or representative from your section. Links to join the meeting will be sent by prior to the meetings.

220128 		Sun, 8/2/2020, -
JSM Walk/Run - Day 1 — Other Cmte/Business
JSM
Organizer(s): Donna LaLonde, American Statistical Association

Join us for the JSM Walk/Run challenge! It is an on demand challenge so it doesn’t matter if you are a morning walker or runner, an evening walker or runner, or any other time of the day. Beginning on Sunday, August 2 and concluding on Thursday, August 6 we will have daily challenges. You can earn 1 point for completing a walk/run, 1 point for completing the daily challenge, and 1 point posting on social media.

We will use this Google sheet to track results: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1D-IYW_KS-INn_bo1iwrW1VTYU5_JOwKYsqElO0cNYIo/edit#gid=0.

Enter your name as a participant and track your daily results. There will be prizes for completing the daily challenge. Every walker or runner who earns 10 points or more will be eligible for the grand prize drawing!

Here are the daily challenges:

Sunday, August 2 - Walk/run 1 mile of a new route + predict how long it will take you to walk or run a mile for the last day. You will need to submit your prediction by 11:59 p.m. ET on Tuesday, August 4

Monday, August 3 - Walk/run 2020 steps or something to do with 2020 (JSM and decennial census for the US)

Tuesday, August 4 - Walk/run a route in the shape of your favorite greek letter. You may submit a map from your fitness device, indicate your route on google maps, or an image of a map showing your route.

Wednesday, August 5 - Walk/run 1 mile, pi kilometers (1.95 miles), pi miles (3.14), or tau miles (6.28 miles)

Thursday, August 6 - Walk/run 1 mile and see how close you are to your prediction.

220130 		Tue, 8/4/2020, -
JSM Walk/Run -Day 3 — Other Cmte/Business
JSM
Organizer(s): Donna LaLonde, American Statistical Association

Join us for the JSM Walk/Run challenge! It is an on demand challenge so it doesn’t matter if you are a morning walker or runner, an evening walker or runner, or any other time of the day. Beginning on Sunday, August 2 and concluding on Thursday, August 6 we will have daily challenges. You can earn 1 point for completing a walk/run, 1 point for completing the daily challenge, and 1 point posting on social media.

Track Your Results

Enter your name as a participant and track your daily results. There will be prizes for completing the daily challenge. Every walker or runner who earns 10 points or more will be eligible for the grand prize drawing!

Here are the daily challenges:

Sunday, August 2 - Walk/run 1 mile of a new route + predict how long it will take you to walk or run a mile for the last day. You will need to submit your prediction by 11:59 p.m. ET on Tuesday, August 4

Monday, August 3 - Walk/run 2020 steps or something to do with 2020 (JSM and decennial census for the US)

Tuesday, August 4 - Walk/run a route in the shape of your favorite greek letter. You may submit a map from your fitness device, indicate your route on google maps, or an image of a map showing your route.

Wednesday, August 5 - Walk/run 1 mile, pi kilometers (1.95 miles), pi miles (3.14), or tau miles (6.28 miles)

Thursday, August 6 - Walk/run 1 mile and see how close you are to your prediction.

220131 		Wed, 8/5/2020, -
JSM Walk/Run - Day 4 — Other Cmte/Business
JSM
Organizer(s): Donna LaLonde, American Statistical Association

Join us for the JSM Walk/Run challenge! It is an on demand challenge so it doesn’t matter if you are a morning walker or runner, an evening walker or runner, or any other time of the day. Beginning on Sunday, August 2 and concluding on Thursday, August 6 we will have daily challenges. You can earn 1 point for completing a walk/run, 1 point for completing the daily challenge, and 1 point posting on social media.

We will use this Google sheet to track results: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1D-IYW_KS-INn_bo1iwrW1VTYU5_JOwKYsqElO0cNYIo/edit#gid=0.

Enter your name as a participant and track your daily results. There will be prizes for completing the daily challenge. Every walker or runner who earns 10 points or more will be eligible for the grand prize drawing!

Here are the daily challenges:

Sunday, August 2 - Walk/run 1 mile of a new route + predict how long it will take you to walk or run a mile for the last day. You will need to submit your prediction by 11:59 p.m. ET on Tuesday, August 4

Monday, August 3 - Walk/run 2020 steps or something to do with 2020 (JSM and decennial census for the US)

Tuesday, August 4 - Walk/run a route in the shape of your favorite greek letter. You may submit a map from your fitness device, indicate your route on google maps, or an image of a map showing your route.

Wednesday, August 5 - Walk/run 1 mile, pi kilometers (1.95 miles), pi miles (3.14), or tau miles (6.28 miles)

Thursday, August 6 - Walk/run 1 mile and see how close you are to your prediction.

220132 		Thu, 8/6/2020, -
JSM Walk/Run - Day 5 — Other Cmte/Business
JSM
Organizer(s): Donna LaLonde, American Statistical Association

Join us for the JSM Walk/Run challenge! It is an on demand challenge so it doesn’t matter if you are a morning walker or runner, an evening walker or runner, or any other time of the day. Beginning on Sunday, August 2 and concluding on Thursday, August 6 we will have daily challenges. You can earn 1 point for completing a walk/run, 1 point for completing the daily challenge, and 1 point posting on social media.

We will use this Google sheet to track results: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1D-IYW_KS-INn_bo1iwrW1VTYU5_JOwKYsqElO0cNYIo/edit#gid=0.

Enter your name as a participant and track your daily results. There will be prizes for completing the daily challenge. Every walker or runner who earns 10 points or more will be eligible for the grand prize drawing!

Here are the daily challenges:

Sunday, August 2 - Walk/run 1 mile of a new route + predict how long it will take you to walk or run a mile for the last day. You will need to submit your prediction by 11:59 p.m. ET on Tuesday, August 4

Monday, August 3 - Walk/run 2020 steps or something to do with 2020 (JSM and decennial census for the US)

Tuesday, August 4 - Walk/run a route in the shape of your favorite greek letter. You may submit a map from your fitness device, indicate your route on google maps, or an image of a map showing your route.

Wednesday, August 5 - Walk/run 1 mile, pi kilometers (1.95 miles), pi miles (3.14), or tau miles (6.28 miles)

Thursday, August 6 - Walk/run 1 mile and see how close you are to your prediction.
